						<summary>

						<p>Below the image of a <hi rend="italic">dvārapālaka</hi> set up close to the inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Airāvatēśvara temple, left of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijayarājēndradēva (Rājādhirāja I).</hi></p>						

						<p>This label inscription in characters of c. 11th century states that this image (<hi rend="italic">dvārapālaka</hi> image) was brought by the king from Kalyāṇapuram after sacking it.</p>						

						<p>(cf: K.A.N. Sastri: <hi rend="italic">Cōḷas,</hi> Vol. I, p. 275 n). </p>						

